'''Agha Saleem''' ({{lang-sd|ÿ¢ÿ∫ÿß ÿ≥ŸÑŸäŸÖ}}; 7 April 1935 ‚Äì 12 April 2016) was a Pakistani writer, novelist, poet, and intellectual of the [[Sindhi language]].<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://dailytimes.com.pk/sindh/12-Apr-16/bilawal-grieved-over-death-of-veteran-writer-agha-saleem |title=Bilawal grieved over death of veteran writer Agha Saleem |website=DailyTimes.com |date=2016-03-21 |accessdate=2016-04-13}}</ref> He was born on 7 April 1935 in [[Shikarpur, Sindh|Shikarpur]]. He joined Radio Pakistan and got retirement from there as station director. After his retirement he joined the field of journalism. He remained the editor of ''[[Daily Sach]]''. He got Shah Latif Award twice and Pride of Performance in 2005 The Shah Abdul Latif Bhittai and Mysticism Award Committee of the academy of letters has selected a book by Agha Saleem, ‚ÄúMelody of Clouds‚Äù, for the cash award for the year2003 .<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.dawn.com/news/141436/hyderabad-agha-saleem-s-book-selected-for-award |title=HYDERABAD: Agha Saleem‚Äôs book selected for award - Newspaper |website=Dawn.com |date=2005-05-31 |accessdate=2016-04-13}}</ref> He died after a prolonged illness on 12 April 2016 in Karachi at the age of 81.<ref>{{cite news|author= |url=http://www.thesindhtimes.com/sindh/renowned-sindhi-writer-novelist-poet-intelectual-agha-saleem-passes-away/ |title=Renowned Sindhi writer, novelist, poet and intelectual &#91;sic&#93; Agha Saleem passes away |newspaper=The Sindh Times|date=2014-06-20 |accessdate=2016-04-13}}</ref>
==See also== *[[Sindhi literature]]
