{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2012}} '''Iseabail Macleod''' [[Order of the British Empire|MBE]] (27 May 1936 in [[Dalmuir]] ‚Äì 15 February 2018 in [[Edinburgh]]<ref>url=http://www.imacleod.com/Ish/</ref>) was a [[Scotland|Scottish]] [[lexicographer]]. Iseabail Macleod was Editorial Director of the [[Scottish National Dictionary Association]] from 1986 to 2002. She received an MBE for services to Scottish dictionaries in the [[2001 New Year Honours]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/in_depth/uk/2000/new_year_honours_2000/1092636.stm|title=MBEs M - R|date=30 December 2000|publisher=|accessdate=27 February 2018|via=news.bbc.co.uk}}</ref> and was an Honorary Fellow of the [[Association for Scottish Literary Studies]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.birlinn.co.uk/Iseabail-Macleod-and-J.-Derrick-McClure-editors/|title=Iseabail Macleod and J. Derrick McClure (editors) :: Authors :: Birlinn Ltd.|website=www.birlinn.co.uk|accessdate=27 February 2018}}</ref> Dying on 15 February 2018, she was cremated on 5 March.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.heraldscotland.com/news/16045216.Iseabail_Macleod/|title=Iseabail Macleod|work=[[The Herald (Glasgow)|The Herald]]|date=24 February 2018|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref>
