{{distinguish|Ki language{{!}}Kombe dialect of Tuki}} {{Infobox language |name=Kombe |nativename=Ngumbi |states=[[Equatorial Guinea]] |ethnicity=[[Kombe people]] |speakers=9,200 |date=2011 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic‚ÄìCongo languages|Atlantic‚ÄìCongo]] |fam3=[[Benue‚ÄìCongo languages|Benue‚ÄìCongo]] |fam4=[[Bantoid languages|Bantoid]] |fam5=[[Bantu languages|Bantu]] ([[Guthrie classification of Bantu languages#Zone A|Zone A]]) |fam6=[[Sawabantu languages|Sawabantu]] (A.30) |fam7=[[yasa language|Yasa]]? |iso3=nui |glotto=ngum1255 |glottorefname=Ngumbi |guthrie=A.33b }}
The '''Kombe language''', or '''Ngumbi''', is a Coastal [[Bantu language]] spoken by the [[Kombe people]] of [[Equatorial Guinea]], one of the [[Ndowe]] peoples of the coast. It is mutually intelligible with [[Yasa language|Yasa]].
