'''List of Hungarian exonyms for places in Slovakia'''. These names are used by the Hungarian ethnic minority in Slovakia, and they are also used in [[Hungary]] and other countries in the Central Europe, which are home of Hungarian minorities. In communities in Slovakia where the ethnic minority represents 20% or more of the population, it has certain cultural and linguistic rights. {| class="wikitable sortable" |- !Place !Hungarian name |- |[[Bratislava]]||[[Pozsony]] |- |[[Ko≈°ice]]||[[Ko≈°ice|Kassa]] |- |[[Pre≈°ov]]||[[Eperjes]] |- |[[≈Ωilina]]||[[Zsolna]] |- |[[Nitra]]||[[Nyitra]] |- |[[Bansk√° Bystrica]]||[[Beszterceb√°nya]] |- |[[Trnava]]||[[Nagyszombat]] |- |[[Martin, Slovakia|Martin]]||[[Tur√≥cszentm√°rton]] |- |[[Trenƒç√≠n]]||[[Trencs√©n]] |- |[[Poprad]]||[[Popr√°d]] |- |[[Prievidza]]||[[Privigye]] |- |[[Zvolen]]||[[Z√≥lyom]] |- |[[Pova≈æsk√° Bystrica]]||[[V√°gbeszterce]] |- |[[Nov√© Z√°mky]]||[[√ârsek√∫jv√°r]] |- |[[Michalovce]]||[[Nagymih√°ly]] |- |[[Spi≈°sk√° Nov√° Ves]]||[[Igl√≥]] |- |[[Kom√°rno]]||[[Kom√°rom]] |- |[[Levice]]||[[L√©va]] |- |[[Humenn√©]]||[[Homonna]] |- |[[Bardejov]]||[[B√°rtfa]] |- |[[Liptovsk√Ω Mikul√°≈°]]||[[Lipt√≥szentmikl√≥s]] |- |[[Ru≈æomberok]]||[[R√≥zsahegy]] |- |[[Pie≈°≈•any]]||[[P√∂sty√©n]] |- |[[Topoƒæƒçany]]||[[Nagytapolcs√°ny]] |- |[[Luƒçenec]]||[[Losonc]] |- |[[ƒåadca]]||[[Csaca]] |- |[[Dubnica nad V√°hom]]||[[M√°riat√∂lgyes]] |- |[[Rimavsk√° Sobota]]||[[Rimaszombat]] |- |[[Partiz√°nske]]||[[Simony]] |- |[[≈†aƒæa, Slovakia|≈†aƒæa]]||[[V√°gsellye]] |- |[[Dunajsk√° Streda]]||[[Dunaszerdahely]] |- |[[Trebi≈°ov]]||[[T≈ëketerebes]] |- |[[Vranov nad Topƒæou]]||[[Varann√≥]] |- |[[Hlohovec]]||[[Galg√≥c]] |- |[[Brezno]]||[[Brezn√≥b√°nya]] |- |[[Snina]]||[[Szinna]] |- |[[Pezinok]]||[[Pezinok|Bazin]] |- |[[Senica]]||[[Szenice]] |- |[[Nov√© Mesto nad V√°hom]]||[[V√°g√∫jhely]] |- |[[B√°novce nad Bebravou]]||[[B√°n]] |- |[[Doln√Ω Kub√≠n]]||[[Als√≥kubin]] |- |[[≈Ωiar nad Hronom]]||[[Garamszentkereszt]] |- |[[Ro≈æ≈àava]]||[[Rozsny√≥]] |- |