{{Infobox language |name=Paasaal |nativename=Southern Sisaala |region=Ghana |speakers=36,000 |date=2003 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic‚ÄìCongo]] |fam3=[[Gur languages|Gur]] |fam4=Southern |fam5=[[Gurunsi languages|Gurunsi]] |fam6=Western |fam7=[[Sisaala language|Sisaala]] |dia1=Gilbagala |dia2=Pasaali |iso3=sig |glotto=paas1238 |glottorefname=Paasaal }}
'''Paasaal''', or Pasaale Sisaala (Southern Sisaala) is a [[Gur languages|Gur]] language of [[Ghana]], with a thousand speakers in Ivory Coast. The two dialects, Gilbagala and Pasaali, are part of a [[dialect continuum]] that continues on into [[Sisaala language|Sisaala]].
